{
    "name": "Monster Hunter",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Monster Hunter",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 227",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 227",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 227
                }
            ],
            "html": "Some mercenaries eschew the complications of politics, oaths of service, and fealty and just get paid to hunt monsters. It's a straightforward form of mercenary service, often dangerous in the extreme, but one that can yield glory and fame.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 22"
        },
        {
            "name": "Mercenaries",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Bribing Mercenaries",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 226
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Unless a mercenary prides themself on their name or reputation, the PCs might be able to bribe them to switch sides, or at least stand aside. You can estimate a bribe by taking roughly 5% of the Party Currency value from the row corresponding to the NPC's level on <a aonid=\"581\" game-obj=\"Rules\">Table 10\u20139</a>."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Mercenary Banter",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 226
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Here's some parlance commonly used by mercenaries. <br/><br/><b>Crackster</b>: Someone adept at breaking locks or safes. <br/><b>Diving</b>: Theft or smuggling below ground, often through tunnels. <br/><b>Foxing</b>: To play at being asleep, usually for an ambush. <br/><b>Medic</b>: A healer. <br/><b>Ram</b>: A hard-hitting warrior. <br/><b>Slinger</b>: A spellcaster. <br/><b>Sway of Coin</b>: Swearing allegiance to whoever pays the most. <br/><b>Waterline</b>: A mercenary troupe's money: \u201cTake time in town while the waterline's high, everyone.\u201d <br/><b>Whisperstep</b>: Anyone who can move stealthily."
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 226
                }
            ],
            "html": "A broad category that includes those wielding arms, spells, or even guile and cunning, mercenaries hire themselves and their expertise to those with the gold to pay for it."
        }
    ],
