                {
                    "name": "Rage",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "<b>Requirements</b> The monster hunter isn't <a aonid=\"15\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">fatigued</a> or raging; <b>Effect</b> The monster hunter gains 9 temporary Hit Points that last until the rage ends. While raging, they deal 8 additional damage with melee attacks, gain a +10-foot status bonus to their Speed, and take a -1 penalty to AC. The monster hunter can't use <a aonid=\"32\" game-obj=\"Traits\">concentrate</a> actions except <a aonid=\"84\" game-obj=\"Actions\">Seek</a> and <a aonid=\"135\" game-obj=\"Traits\">rage</a> actions. The rage lasts for 1 minute, until there are no enemies the monster hunter can perceive, or until the monster hunter falls <a aonid=\"38\" game-obj=\"Conditions\">unconscious</a>. Once the rage ends, the monster hunter can't Rage again for 1 minute.",
